article.headline: San Diego St. 81, New Mexico 76
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Kyle Spain scored a career-high 30 points as San Diego State outlasted New Mexico 81-76 Wednesday for its seventh straight win. The Aztecs (13-4, 3-1 Mountain West Conference) built a 13-point lead late in the second half, but New Mexico cut the lead to two twice in the final 1:17. Lorrenzo Wade made four free throws in the final 34 seconds to seal the win. He finished with 17 points. Phillip McDonald led New Mexico (11-8, 2-2) with 17 points and Tony Danridge added 14. San Diego State trailed by nine early in the first half but used a 15-3 run to lead 37-32 at halftime. The Aztecs extended the lead to 66-53 with 6:13 left before the Lobos rallied in the final minutes.
